# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# .env.example — Environment Variables Template
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# PURPOSE:
#   This is a TEMPLATE showing what variables are needed.
#   It contains NO real values — only placeholder text.
#   This file IS safe to commit to GitHub.
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. Copy this file and rename it to .env
#   2. Fill in your real values
#   3. Never commit the .env file (it's in .gitignore)
#
# To copy via terminal:
#   cp .env.example .env
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── Kit (ConvertKit) Credentials ────────────────────────────────────
# Your Kit API key (Settings → Developer)
KIT_API_KEY=

# Your Kit form ID (found in the form URL)
KIT_FORM_ID=